    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>beef mince </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the beef is browning, dice the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span> </strong>roughly</p><p>Once starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>diced tomato </strong>to the beef and cook for 2-3 min further</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>portobello mushroom tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tortelloni for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the tortelloni, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Tip: Use a ladle to spoon the starchy water from the cooking pasta!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>dried basil </strong>and <strong>dried oregano </strong>to the beef with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and 75ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>bolognese ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>to the bolognese ragù<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up</p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bolognese-ragu-sauce-with-mushroom-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bolognese ragù</strong> <strong>tortelloni </strong>topped with the<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
